{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Billboard'' Year-End Hot 100 singles of 2010}} [[File:Kesha MuchMusic Soundcheck cropped.jpg|thumb|right|190px|[[Ke$ha]]'s single "[[Tik Tok]]" came in at number one, spending nine consecutive weeks at number 1.]] [[File:Katy Perry performing 2010 crop.jpg|thumb|right|190px|Pop singer [[Katy Perry]] has two singles within the top 20, "[[California Gurls]]" and "[[Teenage Dream (Katy Perry song)|Teenage Dream]]", both of which topped the Hot 100 charts.]] [[File:Eminem performing live at dj hero party.jpg|thumb|right|190px|Rapper [[Eminem]] has three singles in the chart, two of his own hits, "[[Not Afraid]]" and "[[Love the Way You Lie]]", as well as [[Drake (entertainer)|Drake's]] "[[Forever (Drake song)|Forever]]".]] [[File:GagaMBTHouston.jpg|thumb|right|190px|Singer [[Lady Gaga]] has four singles within the chart, one of which is her year's highest charted song, "[[Bad Romance]]".]] [[File:David Guetta One Love Tour México.jpg|thumb|right|190px|[[France|French]] DJ [[David Guetta]] has two in the top 40, his own "[[Sexy Bitch]]" with [[Akon]], and a featured "[[Club Can't Handle Me]]" with [[Flo Rida]].]] ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' publishes annual lists of songs based on chart performance over the course of a year based on [[Nielsen Broadcast Data Systems]] and [[Nielsen SoundScan|SoundScan]] information. For 2010, the list for the top 100 [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] [[Billboard Year-End|Year-End]] songs was published on December&nbsp;8, calculated with data from December&nbsp;5, 2009 to November&nbsp;27, 2010. At the number-one position was [[Kesha]]'s "[[Tik Tok]]", which stayed atop the Hot 100 for nine weeks. This achievement made her the first female in the history of the chart to top the Year-End Hot 100 with a debut single.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.billboard.biz/bbbiz/search/article_display.jsp?vnu_content_id=1004134049|title=Lady Gaga Is Billboard's 2010 Artist of the Year; Ke$ha Takes Top New Act|date=December 8, 2010|first=Keith|last=Caulfield|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=December 9, 2010}}</ref>
